AB  - This paper examines the multiperiod capital allocation problem of a corporate division that is subject to ex post financial scrutiny by the parent corporation based upon meeting a specified target rate of return on investment. Using a zero-order decision rule, a deterministic equivalent linear programming model is developed to solve for the division's optimal mix of productive assets and the maturity structure of its debt.
